  "id": "choosing-veneers-or-implants-for-your-teeth",
  "title": "Choosing Veneers or Implants for Your Teeth",
  "slug": "choosing-veneers-or-implants-for-your-teeth",
  "excerpt": "If you want to improve your smile, you may be comparing porcelain veneers and dental implants.  Both solutions can deliver natural-looking results, but they serve different purposes.",
  "content": "<div class=\"prose prose-lg max-w-none\">\n        <p>If you want to improve your smile, you may be comparing porcelain veneers and dental implants. Both solutions can deliver natural-looking results, but they serve different purposes. Understanding how each one works makes it easier to decide which is right for you.</p>\n        <p>Veneers are thin porcelain shells bonded to the front of your teeth. They brighten color, close small gaps, smooth chips, and create a uniform shape. Veneers are ideal when the tooth is healthy but needs cosmetic refinement. Treatment usually takes three visits: a consultation, a preparation appointment with temporary veneers, and a final bonding appointment once the custom porcelain arrives.</p>\n        <p>Implants replace an entire tooth, including the root. A titanium post is placed in the jawbone and topped with a custom crown, bridge, or denture after healing. Implants are the best option when a tooth is missing or cannot be saved. They protect the jawbone, keep nearby teeth from shifting, and look and function like natural teeth.</p>\n        <p>You might need both treatments in one smile makeover. For example, veneers can refresh the front teeth while implants replace missing teeth in the back. We coordinate every step so the color and shape match beautifully.</p>\n        <p>During your consultation we review your goals, evaluate your teeth and gums, and explain the timelines, costs, and maintenance for each option. Together we will build a plan that restores both function and confidence.</p>\n      </div>",
