  "excerpt": "Moving teeth always brings a little tenderness, but Invisalign is designed to keep that feeling as mild as possible.  Most patients notice gentle pressure for a day or two whenever they switch to a new set of aligners.",
  "content": "<div class=\"prose prose-lg max-w-none\">\n        <p>Moving teeth always brings a little tenderness, but Invisalign is designed to keep that feeling as mild as possible. Most patients notice gentle pressure for a day or two whenever they switch to a new set of aligners. The sensation is similar to tight socks—it lets you know progress is happening, then it fades.</p>\n        <p>If a tray feels sharp, we can smooth it, and you can always take the aligners out briefly to brush, eat, or give your mouth a quick break. Staying hydrated, switching to soft foods for a day, and using an over-the-counter pain reliever also help.</p>\n        <p>Because there are no brackets or wires, you avoid the cuts and sores that sometimes come with traditional braces. You control when you remove the aligners, which makes presentations, photos, and special events easier.</p>\n        <p>We tailor each Invisalign plan to your comfort. If you need extra time between aligner changes or want to speed things up with vibration therapy, we will guide you. From the first scan to your final reveal, our team checks in often to make sure you feel confident and cared for.</p>\n      </div>",
