  "excerpt": "Looking for a new dentist can feel overwhelming, but a few simple steps make it easier to find the right fit.  Start by asking friends, coworkers, or your physician which offices they trust.",
  "content": "<div class=\"prose prose-lg max-w-none\">\n        <p>Looking for a new dentist can feel overwhelming, but a few simple steps make it easier to find the right fit. Start by asking friends, coworkers, or your physician which offices they trust. Personal experiences reveal more about communication style and comfort than a long list of online reviews.</p>\n        <p>If you have dental insurance, use your plan’s provider directory to build a shortlist. Then visit each practice’s website and social media accounts to get a sense of their approach. Many offices share photos of their team, treatment rooms, and patient testimonials that give you a better feel for the environment.</p>\n        <p>Before committing, schedule a consultation. Meeting the dentist and team lets you ask questions about services, technology, payment options, and how they handle anxious patients. Pay attention to how you are greeted and how clearly the team explains next steps—those first impressions matter.</p>\n        <p>If you are in the Los Angeles area, our West Hollywood practice offers spa-like comforts alongside advanced dental care. We welcome new patients for relaxed consultations so you can experience the space, meet the team, and decide if we are the right match. Call us to plan your visit.</p>\n      </div>",
