  "excerpt": "Porcelain veneers are an investment in a brighter, more confident smile.  In Los Angeles, high-quality veneers typically range from $1,800 to $2,500 per tooth.",
  "content": "<div class=\"prose prose-lg max-w-none\">\n        <p>Porcelain veneers are an investment in a brighter, more confident smile. In Los Angeles, high-quality veneers typically range from $1,800 to $2,500 per tooth. Many patients choose to treat 8–10 teeth that show when they smile, while others refresh their full arch for complete symmetry. During your consultation we provide a detailed estimate based on your goals, the number of veneers, and any preparatory care needed.</p>\n        <p>Why do veneers cost more than whitening or bonding? Premium porcelain looks and feels like natural enamel, resists stains, and is handcrafted by expert ceramists. Combined with digital planning and a cosmetic dentist’s artistry, veneers deliver a customized result that lasts a decade or longer with good care.</p>\n        <p>Insurance often considers veneers elective, but we review every plan to see if any portion—such as restorations on damaged teeth—can be covered. We also offer flexible payment options to make treatment more comfortable.</p>\n        <p>Curious what your dream smile would cost? Schedule a consultation. We will design a personalized plan, share a preview of your results, and walk you through timing, pricing, and financing step by step.</p>\n        <p>A brilliant smile is priceless. Here in Los Angeles, celebrities and business leaders are famous for the smiles their careers are built on. If you want a world-class smile, this city is the place to make it happen.</p>\n        <p>Celebrities worldwide achieve this with porcelain veneers , a dental treatment for shaping, aligning, and coloring their teeth with a completely natural appearance. So what is the cost of dental veneers in Los Angeles, and what makes them worth it?</p>\n        <h2>Price of the Highest-Quality Dental Veneers</h2>\n        <p>Typical Cost: About $20,000 for a 10-unit veneer design.</p>\n        <h2>Cost for All Teeth:</h2>\n        <p>About $50,000 for a 32-unit veneer design Cost per Tooth: $1800 to $2500 The cost can be dependant on the number of teeth treated. The price may also vary due to diagnostic costs and the delivery method that is used.</p>\n        <h2>Why The Best Dental Veneers are Well-Worth the Price</h2>\n        <h2>A Natural Look</h2>\n        <p>Top-quality porcelain veneers are virtually indistinguishable from natural teeth.</p>\n        <p>World-Class Comfort Exquisite Dentistry in West Hollywood is the original dental spa. Even enjoy music or Netflix.</p>\n        <h2>An Exceptional Dentist</h2>\n        <p>Dr. Aguil will work with you every step of the way to design your ideal smile with an expert touch.</p>\n        <p>Advanced Technology On your very first visit, our iTero scanner shows you what your teeth will look like after treatment is complete.</p>\n        <h2>Restore Your Smile’s Brilliance</h2>\n        <p>With your smile the best it’s ever looked, your confidence will be at an all-time high CONTACT EXQUISITE DENTISTRY (323) 272-2388 Call to schedule your cosmetic dentist appointment and experience true luxury.</p>\n        <h2>Stay Away from Budget Veneers</h2>\n        <p>Top-quality porcelain veneers at Exquisite Dentistry are made at one of the best dental labs in the United States and fitted by a leading cosmetic dentist. But not every set of veneers is made with the same quality and care. You could go with one of these other options to cut down on the cost of veneers for your teeth, but it’s not recommended.</p>\n        <p>Discount veneers cut all sorts of corners. They’re often made in China, and not well-customized to fit your mouth. Expect to see that fake plastic look; the color gives them away every time. And forget reliability. High-end porcelain veneers are expected to last a decade or longer, but you’ll need to replace cheap veneers much sooner than you expect.</p>\n        <p>Save yourself the trouble, the pain, and the potential embarrassment of low-cost veneers on your teeth. Get your cosmetic dentistry done right.</p>\n        <h2>How Dental Insurance Factors Into the Cost</h2>\n        <p>Insurance companies try to only pay for what they have to. Veneers may have a fantastic impact on your life and career, but they’re mostly seen as elective procedures in the eyes of insurance companies. It’s unlikely that the cost of dental veneers will be covered by your insurance.</p>\n        <p>If medically indicated, the partial cost of veneers for some of your teeth may be covered as crown repair or crown replacement. Dr. Aguil at Exquisite Dentistry will work with you to make the most of your insurance .</p>\n        <h2>Consult on Your Treatment with Dental Veneers</h2>\n        <p>Dr. Aguil and his team will help you achieve the smile you’ve always wanted with attentive, personalized care. Treatment with dental veneers can often be completed in as few as 3 visits. Expect the most comfortable experience you’ve ever had at the dentist.</p>\n        <h2>Call</h2>\n        <p>(323) 272-2388 to schedule your appointment with Exquisite Dentistry in Los Angeles.</p>\n      </div>",
